{{Documentation subpage}} <!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE. --> The [[Wikipedia:External links|external links guideline]] recommends [[WP:ELNO|avoiding links to Facebook]] unless the profile is an [[WP:ELOFFICIAL|official account]], "controlled by the subject (organization or individual person) of the Wikipedia article".
==Usage== The first parameter for the {{tl|Facebook user}} template is the name of the Facebook account. This can be found in the page's [[Uniform Resource Locator|URL]]. For example: if the URL is <tt><nowiki>http://www.facebook.com/example</nowiki></tt>, then the account name is ''example''. The second parameter is the description or display name.
== Examples == In this example, the Facebook user account is ''markzuckerberg'' and the description in the link is ''Mark Zuckerberg'': <nowiki>{{Facebook User|markzuckerberg|Mark Zuckerberg}}</nowiki> {{Facebook User|markzuckerberg|Mark Zuckerberg}}
In this example, there's an ID instead of user name: <nowiki>{{Facebook User|id=markzuckerberg/68310606562|name=Mark Zuckerberg}}</nowiki> {{Facebook User|id=markzuckerberg/68310606562|name=Mark Zuckerberg}}
